MANDATORY ATTRIBUTION CONDITIONS

The following attribution conditions are NON-NEGOTIABLE, binding, and
enforceable. Any deviation constitutes copyright infringement and
immediate license termination. These conditions apply to ALL uses,
whether the Storefront is:
  • Public or private
  • Commercial or non-commercial
  • Self-hosted, cloud-hosted, or SaaS
  • Modified or unmodified

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
CONDITION 1 — README/DOCUMENTATION ATTRIBUTION (Code Repository)
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

If you deploy or distribute this Storefront Software (modified or not), your
project's primary documentation file MUST contain a clearly visible, dedicated
attribution section that includes ALL of the following fields, exactly as
written and in this order:

    ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
    │ Built on Himanshu's E-Commerce Storefront Framework    │
    │ Original author: Himanshu (https://github.com/Newbie-Himanshu) │
    │ Source: https://github.com/Newbie-Himanshu/vridhira... │
    │ License: E-Commerce Storefront Attribution License v2.0│
    └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

MANDATORY PROPERTIES:
  ✓ All four fields MUST be present, unmodified, in exact order
  ✓ Visible without expanding collapsed sections or hidden elements
  ✓ Hyperlinks must be ACTIVE and working
  ✓ Appear in the PRIMARY documentation (README.md, INSTALL.md, or landing page)
  ✓ Appear ABOVE the fold (within first 50% of document)
  ✓ Applied in a contrasting color (minimum 4.5:1 contrast ratio with background)
  ✓ Font size minimum 11px
  ✓ No disclaimer or qualification permitted (e.g., "Inspired by..." or "Based loosely on..." are NOT acceptable)

VIOLATIONS include:
  • Paraphrasing or summarizing the attribution text
  • Moving attribution to secondary documents (CHANGELOG, LICENSE only, footer comments)
  • Removing hyperlinks or replacing them with non-functional text
  • Abbreviating URLs or project names
  • Prefixing with disclaimers like "Uses code from..." or "Includes..."

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
CONDITION 2 — LIVE UI CREDITS FOOTER (Deployed Storefronts)
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

IF AND ONLY IF you deploy a live, publicly accessible storefront application
(website, mobile app, PWA, or any customer-facing interface), the Storefront
MUST display an attribution credit block at ALL TIMES, visible on every page
without exception.

REQUIRED CREDIT BLOCK PROPERTIES:
  (a) PLACEMENT: Footer section of every page
      ✗ NOT: Header, sidebar, hidden modal, collapsible menu, or off-screen
      ✓ Visible on initial page load without user interaction
      ✓ Persists across all pages and navigation states

  (b) CONTENT: Must include at minimum:
      • Crediting text: "Storefront powered by Himanshu"
      • Active hyperlink to: https://github.com/Newbie-Himanshu
      • Explicit reference to this License
      (Example: "Built with Himanshu's Storefront Framework - License v2.0")

  (c) LEGIBILITY REQUIREMENTS (STRICTLY ENFORCED):
      • Font-size: MINIMUM 11px (measured in user agent resolution)
      • Color contrast ratio: MINIMUM 4.5:1 against background
      • Font weight: NORMAL or BOLD (not thin/100-300 weight)
      • Line height: MINIMUM 1.4em
      • Letter spacing: Not compressed below default browser rendering

  (d) PROHIBITED VISIBILITY TECHNIQUES (each is a violation):
      ✗ display: none, visibility: hidden, opacity < 0.8
      ✗ position: absolute/fixed with off-screen coordinates (-9999px, etc.)
      ✗ z-index: negative or layered behind other elements
      ✗ pointer-events: none, user-select: none, or text-indent tricks
      ✗ Color matching text to background (#FFF on white, etc.)
      ✗ Negative text-indent or transform: translateX(-9999px)
      ✗ width: 0, height: 0, or overflow: hidden wrappers
      ✗ max-height: 0, max-width: 0
      ✗ Removing from DOM via JavaScript after page load
      ✗ Conditional hiding based on user behavior or geography
      ✗ Hiding in browsers/devices where you assume users won't notice
      ✗ Any other CSS, HTML, or JavaScript technique that reduces visibility

  (e) RUNTIME VERIFICATION:
      The credit block MUST be detectable by:
      • Visual inspection of the deployed application
      • CSS inspection (computed styles) showing proper visibility
      • DOM analysis showing element is rendered and in viewport
      • Automated accessibility tools must detect the text

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
CONDITION 3 — SOURCE CODE COPYRIGHT HEADER PRESERVATION (Non-Removal Clause)
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

All copies or substantial portions of the Storefront Software MUST retain:

  (a) This LICENSE file in full, unmodified, in the root of the repository
  (b) Every source file containing Licensor copyright notices MUST preserve:
      • Original copyright line: (c) 2026 Himanshu
      • Reference to this License
      • Original author attribution
      This header is often located at the top of JavaScript/React/TypeScript files

  (c) You MAY:
      • Add your own copyright notices ABOVE the existing ones
      • Add comments explaining your modifications
      • Refactor the code's internal structure

  (d) You MAY NOT:
      • Remove, comment-out, or hide the original copyright header
      • Replace the header with your own copyright (you may only ADD above)
      • Modify the author name or remove "Himanshu" reference
      • Move the header to a separate file or comment block that obscures it
      • Delete or rewrite the LICENSE file
      • Claim the Software as original work unless it is a substantial,
        independently-created derivative

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
CONDITION 4 — COMPONENTS & IMPORTS ATTRIBUTION
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

If you include, import, or use any identifiable components, modules, or
utilities originally from this Storefront Software (e.g., custom checkout
flow, cart state management, product catalog display, payment integration),
you MUST:

  (a) Identify these components in comments or documentation:
      // Based on Himanshu's Storefront Framework - [component name]
      // Original source: https://github.com/Newbie-Himanshu/...

  (b) Maintain a COMPONENTS_ORIGIN.md file documenting:
      • Original component name
      • Current name (if changed)
      • Whether modified (Y/N) and how
      • Link to original source

  (c) You MAY NOT:
      • Completely rewrite component logic to obscure its origin
      • Claim custom components as original work if substantially based
        on this Software
      • Hide component sources through obfuscation

